{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":368,"text":"We have a global health challenge"},{"time":2505,"text":"in our hands today,"},{"time":4197,"text":"and that is that the way we currently"},{"time":7257,"text":"discover and develop new drugs"},{"time":10182,"text":"is too costly, takes far too long,"},{"time":14360,"text":"and it fails more often than it succeeds."},{"time":18074,"text":"It really just isn't working, and that means"},{"time":21451,"text":"that patients that badly need new therapies"},{"time":24498,"text":"are not getting them,"},{"time":26209,"text":"and diseases are going untreated."},{"time":29707,"text":"We seem to be spending more and more money."},{"time":32790,"text":"So for every billion dollars we spend in R&amp;D,"},{"time":36886,"text":"we're getting less drugs approved into the market."},{"time":40715,"text":"More money, less drugs. Hmm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43932,"text":"So what's going on here?"},{"time":45852,"text":"Well, there's a multitude of factors at play,"},{"time":48447,"text":"but I think one of the key factors"},{"time":50468,"text":"is that the tools that we currently have"},{"time":52865,"text":"available to test whether a drug is going to work,"},{"time":56948,"text":"whether it has efficacy,"},{"time":58337,"text":"or whether it's going to be safe"},{"time":60103,"text":"before we get it into human clinical trials,"},{"time":63655,"text":"are failing us. They're not predicting"},{"time":65806,"text":"what's going to happen in humans."},{"time":69034,"text":"And we have two main tools available"},{"time":71757,"text":"at our disposal."},{"time":73771,"text":"They are cells in dishes and animal testing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77812,"text":"Now let's talk about the first one, cells in dishes."},{"time":81132,"text":"So, cells are happily functioning in our bodies."},{"time":84285,"text":"We take them and rip them out"},{"time":86340,"text":"of their native environment,\nthrow them in one of these dishes,"},{"time":89289,"text":"and expect them to work."},{"time":90874,"text":"Guess what. They don't."},{"time":93067,"text":"They don't like that environment"},{"time":94729,"text":"because it's nothing like"},{"time":96361,"text":"what they have in the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99037,"text":"What about animal testing?"},{"time":101108,"text":"Well, animals do and can provide"},{"time":103993,"text":"extremely useful information."},{"time":106255,"text":"They teach us about what happens"},{"time":107964,"text":"in the complex organism."},{"time":110293,"text":"We learn more about the biology itself."},{"time":113301,"text":"However, more often than not,"},{"time":116199,"text":"animal models fail to predict\nwhat will happen in humans"},{"time":120415,"text":"when they're treated with a particular drug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123601,"text":"So we need better tools."},{"time":125980,"text":"We need human cells,"},{"time":127733,"text":"but we need to find a way to keep them happy"},{"time":130483,"text":"outside the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132074,"text":"Our bodies are dynamic environments."},{"time":134980,"text":"We're in constant motion."},{"time":136820,"text":"Our cells experience that."},{"time":139011,"text":"They're in dynamic environments in our body."},{"time":141820,"text":"They're under constant mechanical forces."},{"time":144575,"text":"So if we want to make cells happy"},{"time":147031,"text":"outside our bodies,"},{"time":148460,"text":"we need to become cell architects."},{"time":150986,"text":"We need to design, build and engineer"},{"time":155330,"text":"a home away from home for the cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158561,"text":"And at the Wyss Institute,"},{"time":160235,"text":"we've done just that."},{"time":162173,"text":"We call it an organ-on-a-chip."},{"time":165197,"text":"And I have one right here."},{"time":166988,"text":"It's beautiful, isn't it?\nBut it's pretty incredible."},{"time":169803,"text":"Right here in my hand is a breathing, living"},{"time":174303,"text":"human lung on a chip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176961,"text":"And it's not just beautiful."},{"time":179089,"text":"It can do a tremendous amount of things."},{"time":181529,"text":"We have living cells in that little chip,"},{"time":185308,"text":"cells that are in a dynamic environment"},{"time":187858,"text":"interacting with different cell types."},{"time":190939,"text":"There's been many people"},{"time":192578,"text":"trying to grow cells in the lab."},{"time":194439,"text":"They've tried many different approaches."},{"time":197595,"text":"They've even tried to grow\nlittle mini-organs in the lab."},{"time":200222,"text":"We're not trying to do that here."},{"time":201771,"text":"We're simply trying to recreate"},{"time":203897,"text":"in this tiny chip"},{"time":205474,"text":"the smallest functional unit"},{"time":208491,"text":"that represents the biochemistry,"},{"time":211045,"text":"the function and the mechanical strain"},{"time":214169,"text":"that the cells experience in our bodies."},{"time":217685,"text":"So how does it work? Let me show you."},{"time":220717,"text":"We use techniques from the computer chip"},{"time":223351,"text":"manufacturing industry"},{"time":224984,"text":"to make these structures at a scale"},{"time":227181,"text":"relevant to both the cells and their environment."},{"time":230077,"text":"We have three fluidic channels."},{"time":232141,"text":"In the center, we have a porous, flexible membrane"},{"time":235853,"text":"on which we can add human cells"},{"time":237916,"text":"from, say, our lungs,"},{"time":239260,"text":"and then underneath, they had capillary cells,"},{"time":241747,"text":"the cells in our blood vessels."},{"time":243535,"text":"And we can then apply mechanical forces to the chip"},{"time":247855,"text":"that stretch and contract the membrane,"},{"time":250684,"text":"so the cells experience the same mechanical forces"},{"time":253781,"text":"that they did when we breathe."},{"time":256714,"text":"And they experience them how they did in the body."},{"time":259874,"text":"There's air flowing through the top channel,"},{"time":262274,"text":"and then we flow a liquid that contains nutrients"},{"time":265623,"text":"through the blood channel."},{"time":268462,"text":"Now the chip is really beautiful,"},{"time":270834,"text":"but what can we do with it?"},{"time":272931,"text":"We can get incredible functionality"},{"time":275255,"text":"inside these little chips."},{"time":277006,"text":"Let me show you."},{"time":278512,"text":"We could, for example, mimic infection,"},{"time":281143,"text":"where we add bacterial cells into the lung."},{"time":284679,"text":"then we can add human white blood cells."},{"time":287611,"text":"White blood cells are our body's defense"},{"time":290202,"text":"against bacterial invaders,"},{"time":291570,"text":"and when they sense this\ninflammation due to infection,"},{"time":294739,"text":"they will enter from the blood into the lung"},{"time":297596,"text":"and engulf the bacteria."},{"time":299511,"text":"Well now you're going to see this happening"},{"time":301759,"text":"live in an actual human lung on a chip."},{"time":305069,"text":"We've labeled the white blood cells\nso you can see them flowing through,"},{"time":308612,"text":"and when they detect that infection,"},{"time":310773,"text":"they begin to stick."},{"time":312170,"text":"They stick, and then they try to go into the lung"},{"time":316057,"text":"side from blood channel."},{"time":317838,"text":"And you can see here, we can actually visualize"},{"time":321527,"text":"a single white blood cell."},{"time":325286,"text":"It sticks, it wiggles its way through"},{"time":327542,"text":"between the cell layers, through the pore,"},{"time":329857,"text":"comes out on the other side of the membrane,"},{"time":332278,"text":"and right there, it's going to engulf the bacteria"},{"time":335713,"text":"labeled in green."},{"time":337362,"text":"In that tiny chip, you just witnessed"},{"time":340366,"text":"one of the most fundamental responses"},{"time":343547,"text":"our body has to an infection."},{"time":345504,"text":"It's the way we respond to -- an immune response."},{"time":349274,"text":"It's pretty exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351675,"text":"Now I want to share this picture with you,"},{"time":354018,"text":"not just because it's so beautiful,"},{"time":356656,"text":"but because it tells us an enormous\namount of information"},{"time":359992,"text":"about what the cells are doing within the chips."},{"time":362589,"text":"It tells us that these cells"},{"time":364848,"text":"from the small airways in our lungs,"},{"time":367159,"text":"actually have these hairlike structures"},{"time":368910,"text":"that you would expect to see in the lung."},{"time":370918,"text":"These structures are called cilia,"},{"time":372383,"text":"and they actually move the mucus out of the lung."},{"time":375293,"text":"Yeah. Mucus. Yuck."},{"time":376832,"text":"But mucus is actually very important."},{"time":379272,"text":"Mucus traps particulates, viruses,"},{"time":381853,"text":"potential allergens,"},{"time":383312,"text":"and these little cilia move"},{"time":384913,"text":"and clear the mucus out."},{"time":387163,"text":"When they get damaged, say,"},{"time":389075,"text":"by cigarette smoke for example,"},{"time":391494,"text":"they don't work properly,\nand they can't clear that mucus out."},{"time":394302,"text":"And that can lead to diseases such as bronchitis."},{"time":398119,"text":"Cilia and the clearance of mucus"},{"time":400766,"text":"are also involved in awful diseases like cystic fibrosis."},{"time":405227,"text":"But now, with the functionality\nthat we get in these chips,"},{"time":408777,"text":"we can begin to look"},{"time":410601,"text":"for potential new treatments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413114,"text":"We didn't stop with the lung on a chip."},{"time":415066,"text":"We have a gut on a chip."},{"time":416950,"text":"You can see one right here."},{"time":418980,"text":"And we've put intestinal human cells"},{"time":422206,"text":"in a gut on a chip,"},{"time":424111,"text":"and they're under constant peristaltic motion,"},{"time":426948,"text":"this trickling flow through the cells,"},{"time":430139,"text":"and we can mimic many of the functions"},{"time":432697,"text":"that you actually would expect to see"},{"time":434960,"text":"in the human intestine."},{"time":436653,"text":"Now we can begin to create models of diseases"},{"time":440444,"text":"such as irritable bowel syndrome."},{"time":442854,"text":"This is a disease that affects"},{"time":444936,"text":"a large number of individuals."},{"time":446847,"text":"It's really debilitating,"},{"time":448621,"text":"and there aren't really many good treatments for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452563,"text":"Now we have a whole pipeline"},{"time":454865,"text":"of different organ chips"},{"time":457144,"text":"that we are currently working on in our labs."},{"time":460876,"text":"Now, the true power of this technology, however,"},{"time":464295,"text":"really comes from the fact"},{"time":466420,"text":"that we can fluidically link them."},{"time":468965,"text":"There's fluid flowing across these cells,"},{"time":470912,"text":"so we can begin to interconnect"},{"time":472991,"text":"multiple different chips together"},{"time":475853,"text":"to form what we call a virtual human on a chip."},{"time":480066,"text":"Now we're really getting excited."},{"time":483075,"text":"We're not going to ever recreate \na whole human in these chips,"},{"time":487170,"text":"but what our goal is is to be able to recreate"},{"time":491339,"text":"sufficient functionality"},{"time":493352,"text":"so that we can make better predictions"},{"time":495712,"text":"of what's going to happen in humans."},{"time":497926,"text":"For example, now we can begin to explore"},{"time":500850,"text":"what happens when we put\na drug like an aerosol drug."},{"time":504284,"text":"Those of you like me who have asthma,\nwhen you take your inhaler,"},{"time":507270,"text":"we can explore how that drug comes into your lungs,"},{"time":510196,"text":"how it enters the body,"},{"time":511822,"text":"how it might affect, say, your heart."},{"time":513576,"text":"Does it change the beating of your heart?"},{"time":515484,"text":"Does it have a toxicity?"},{"time":517125,"text":"Does it get cleared by the liver?"},{"time":519133,"text":"Is it metabolized in the liver?"},{"time":521285,"text":"Is it excreted in your kidneys?"},{"time":523176,"text":"We can begin to study the dynamic"},{"time":525388,"text":"response of the body to a drug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528028,"text":"This could really revolutionize"},{"time":529947,"text":"and be a game changer"},{"time":531596,"text":"for not only the pharmaceutical industry,"},{"time":534534,"text":"but a whole host of different industries,"},{"time":536907,"text":"including the cosmetics industry."},{"time":539307,"text":"We can potentially use the skin on a chip"},{"time":542189,"text":"that we're currently developing in the lab"},{"time":544150,"text":"to test whether the ingredients in those products"},{"time":546704,"text":"that you're using are actually \nsafe to put on your skin"},{"time":549987,"text":"without the need for animal testing."},{"time":552676,"text":"We could test the safety"},{"time":554620,"text":"of chemicals that we are exposed to"},{"time":556873,"text":"on a daily basis in our environment,"},{"time":558787,"text":"such as chemicals in regular household cleaners."},{"time":562518,"text":"We could also use the organs on chips"},{"time":565720,"text":"for applications in bioterrorism"},{"time":568499,"text":"or radiation exposure."},{"time":571070,"text":"We could use them to learn more about"},{"time":574420,"text":"diseases such as ebola"},{"time":577464,"text":"or other deadly diseases such as SARS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581356,"text":"Organs on chips could also change"},{"time":583194,"text":"the way we do clinical trials in the future."},{"time":586568,"text":"Right now, the average participant"},{"time":589155,"text":"in a clinical trial is that: average."},{"time":592525,"text":"Tends to be middle aged, tends to be female."},{"time":595851,"text":"You won't find many clinical trials"},{"time":598323,"text":"in which children are involved,"},{"time":599838,"text":"yet every day, we give children medications,"},{"time":603385,"text":"and the only safety data we have on that drug"},{"time":607131,"text":"is one that we obtained from adults."},{"time":610205,"text":"Children are not adults."},{"time":611999,"text":"They may not respond in the same way adults do."},{"time":615132,"text":"There are other things like genetic differences"},{"time":617544,"text":"in populations"},{"time":618977,"text":"that may lead to at-risk populations"},{"time":622083,"text":"that are at risk of having an adverse drug reaction."},{"time":625520,"text":"Now imagine if we could take cells\nfrom all those different populations,"},{"time":628919,"text":"put them on chips,"},{"time":630827,"text":"and create populations on a chip."},{"time":632791,"text":"This could really change the way"},{"time":634629,"text":"we do clinical trials."},{"time":636698,"text":"And this is the team and the people\nthat are doing this."},{"time":639530,"text":"We have engineers, we have cell biologists,"},{"time":642787,"text":"we have clinicians, all working together."},{"time":646561,"text":"We're really seeing something quite incredible"},{"time":648487,"text":"at the Wyss Institute."},{"time":650092,"text":"It's really a convergence of disciplines,"},{"time":652263,"text":"where biology is influencing the way we design,"},{"time":655983,"text":"the way we engineer, the way we build."},{"time":658645,"text":"It's pretty exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660048,"text":"We're establishing important industry collaborations"},{"time":663612,"text":"such as the one we have with a company"},{"time":666985,"text":"that has expertise in large-scale\ndigital manufacturing."},{"time":670584,"text":"They're going to help us make,"},{"time":672603,"text":"instead of one of these,"},{"time":674129,"text":"millions of these chips,"},{"time":675712,"text":"so that we can get them into the hands"},{"time":677381,"text":"of as many researchers as possible."},{"time":680270,"text":"And this is key to the potential of that technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684486,"text":"Now let me show you our instrument."},{"time":687023,"text":"This is an instrument that our engineers"},{"time":689012,"text":"are actually prototyping right now in the lab,"},{"time":691630,"text":"and this instrument is going to give us"},{"time":693939,"text":"the engineering controls that we're going to require"},{"time":696398,"text":"in order to link 10 or more organ chips together."},{"time":700566,"text":"It does something else that's very important."},{"time":702795,"text":"It creates an easy user interface."},{"time":705639,"text":"So a cell biologist like me can come in,"},{"time":708629,"text":"take a chip, put it in a cartridge"},{"time":710637,"text":"like the prototype you see there,"},{"time":712569,"text":"put the cartridge into the machine"},{"time":714640,"text":"just like you would a C.D.,"},{"time":716128,"text":"and away you go."},{"time":717260,"text":"Plug and play. Easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720009,"text":"Now, let's imagine a little bit"},{"time":722523,"text":"what the future might look like"},{"time":723902,"text":"if I could take your stem cells"},{"time":726315,"text":"and put them on a chip,"},{"time":727755,"text":"or your stem cells and put them on a chip."},{"time":730974,"text":"It would be a personalized chip just for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734475,"text":"Now all of us in here are individuals,"},{"time":737683,"text":"and those individual differences mean"},{"time":740521,"text":"that we could react very differently"},{"time":742963,"text":"and sometimes in unpredictable ways to drugs."},{"time":747210,"text":"I myself, a couple of years back,\nhad a really bad headache,"},{"time":751778,"text":"just couldn't shake it, thought, \n\"Well, I'll try something different.\""},{"time":754191,"text":"I took some Advil. Fifteen minutes later,"},{"time":756326,"text":"I was on my way to the emergency room"},{"time":758206,"text":"with a full-blown asthma attack."},{"time":760099,"text":"Now, obviously it wasn't fatal,"},{"time":761929,"text":"but unfortunately, some of these"},{"time":765102,"text":"adverse drug reactions can be fatal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768711,"text":"So how do we prevent them?"},{"time":770652,"text":"Well, we could imagine one day"},{"time":773232,"text":"having Geraldine on a chip,"},{"time":775575,"text":"having Danielle on a chip,"},{"time":777324,"text":"having you on a chip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778797,"text":"Personalized medicine. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781185,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}